The course gives an overview of Estonian literature. The most important sub-topics are Estonian literature during the last twenty-five years, in parallel with exile literature and literature from the first period of independence, in the Estonian SSR.Objectives/eesmärkid:  To provide an overview of Estonian literature, starting from the most popular literary works of modern times and finishing with the literary works of the first period of independence. Become acquainted with screenings of major literary works.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  .Student 1) knows the main features of Estonian literature; 2) is able to  dissert central Estonian writers and works in historical context; 3) can distinguish the most important literary trends; 4) has read the most important fictional texts from the period under review and has viewed their screenings.
